  <title>Cam Follower Motion</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Cam-Follower Motion<keyword>Indexing</keyword><keyword>Oscillating</keyword><keyword>Reciprocating</keyword><keyword>Translating</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="2" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Cam-Follower Motion</text><text styleclass="Interface-Small" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">: </text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Since a</text><text style="font-weight:normal;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Cam-Follower</text><text style="font-weight:normal;"> is any </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal;"> (but not a </text><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Connecting Part</text><text style="font-weight:normal;">) </text>in a kinematic-chain, the motion of a Cam-Follower is very general. It may be:</para>
          <list id="4" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted - compressed2" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted - compressed2">specified directly with a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion FB</text>, and <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-Motion-Dimension" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion-Dimension FB</link><text styleclass="Popup Box">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted - compressed2">from the measured motion of a different Part in a different kinematic-chain</li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted - compressed2">stationary</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Cam-Follower-Shape">Cam-Follower Shapes</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Interface">Indexing:</text> moves, then dwells, then moves again. An integer number of moves complete one rotation. The usual term for <text styleclass="VariableName-small">move</text> is <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Index.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Interface">Oscillating:</text> swings back-and-forth.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Reciprocating</text>: slides back-and-forth<text style="font-style:normal;">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
